{
  "stem": "7860.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They directed me to an orphanage in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And these were children who survived in the forest.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Jewish children in their orphanage after the Russians came in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And they asked me the word [YIDDISH] I didn't speak Yiddish-- now that I know what [YIDDISH] meant until recently.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they wanted to see if I'm circumcised.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Now the Gentiles want to see if I'm circumcised, these guys want to see if I'm circumcised, and I had a fight with them.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I walked out in disgust after beating up some boys over there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And I walk out in disgust.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And a little boy named Chaim Boorstein, he followed me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "He looked very Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And him and I were going to hitchhike towards the United States.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not after the war.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The war is still going on but the Russians were there already occupying the area.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And going back to the German occupation, if you wish me to continue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had many, many collaborators.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If not the collaborators, many, many Jews could have survived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A Jew could not possible-- even if he had fictitious papers-- he couldn't survive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A German would never recognize me because of my Jewish accent.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well I had to learn how to speak Polish very quick with a Gentile accent.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Which I still speak like one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And a Pole would recognize it and turn us in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A Jew-- I, my personal opinion is all the extermination camps were built in Poland.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "A Jew who have he escaped off the trains, there were collaborators picking him off the trains and handing him over.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Would have been the only reward to them was for a human life to take the person's shoes or his clothing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one time I am-- I discovered two other boys.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
